4 insurance plan participation and sign an affidavit attesting that
5 the participant is currently covered and does not require state-
6 provided health insurance each plan year. Any active employee
7 opting out of the state's basic plan or the health and dental basic
8 plan options pursuant to this section shall receive One Hundred
9 Fifty Dollars ($150.00) in lieu of the flexible benefit amount the
10 employee would be otherwise eligible to receive. Any savings
11 realized by the state as a result of a participant opting out of
12 health insurance plan coverage shall be retained by the state.
13 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
